9/7/99
  - Remove PROG_REFRESH compilation flag, and entryOnIPic global variable.
  - Unified the usage of procId: ppcId, myId, muxId.
  - Restructured control.c
  - Used new channel mode definition
    - simplified Bufferer task
  - Added START_PIDGRP, STOP_PIDGRP, DEL_PIDGRP and SWITCH_CANCEL
  - New mux can now accept PID without data.  Therefore no need for
    special treatment of AD channel.
 
  - New task structure to support multi-channel DPI:
      - Control Task directly send switchPidGrpReq to switcher Task
      - Switcher Task check request for error, and generate corresponding
        ACK/NAK to PPC.
      - Switcher Task signal to SpliceResp Task thru spReqSema and spReqQue.
      - On receiving spReqSema, SpliceResp Task wait for spDoneSema, which 
        will also be generate by SwitcherTask.  The wait timeout in 50 ms.
      - If wait in SpliceResp Task timeouts, all pending splice request will
        be examined for actual timeout.  If so, SpliceResp Task will issue
        a SpliceCancel command to Switcher Task.
      - Switcher Task, on receiving the SpliceCancel command, will terminate
        the splice operation, and send back a spDone sema to SpliceResp Task.

    Advantages for this approach:
      - Only one SpliceResp Task is needed to support multiple channel DPI.
        No need for the original Splice Control Task.
      - No need to mutual exclusive sema between Switcher and Splice Control
        tasks.


