  How to support frame-based switching:
    Assumption: spliceFrm should contains integer number of anchor units.
                For example, if spliceFrm=n, then the n+1 picture, if exists,
                should not be a B picture.
    With this assumption, same results will be obtained counting by transmitted
    frames or displayed frames.

    Set spliceTime to the PET of the n-th picture of the FG channel.  From this
    point on, everything will be the same as time based switching.

  One problem of the current splice algoirthm is that for BG channel, the
  spliceTime is initialized to the requested splice time.  Ultimately, it
  should be set slightly earlier than the requested splice time so as to
  allow more precisely splice operation.

                            request ST
                                 |
                                 |   +- exit point
                                 v   v
             FG                     P
                 ----------------------------------
             BG                I
                              ^
                              |
                         entry point

  To solve this issue, we initialize the spliceTime of BG channel to be
  requested splice time - BG channel acquisition time.
  (Tried but doesn't really improve the response time yet.  Postponed.)

